blog.name: cutesysoft
blog.title: It be like that sometimes
blog.description: Dan and Phil (and BTS) fanfic in the making 🖋️ I DON'T OWN BTS, DAN HOWELL or PHIL LESTER MASTERLIST

body:
GASHINA (Dan x female reader) chapter 3

After breaking up with his girlfriend, Dan travelled to Seoul where he heard the lines, Gashina for the first time. His journey of recovering from the break up began there with the help of a special girl who will fix his broken heart.

You could feel Dan staring at you sitting across him with then Sun glaring at your features making it irresistible to men around you. You felt his stare and so you looked up from your drink you ordered, your cheeks heating up when you saw his flushed ones. He avoided eye contact with you for the whole time after you caught him staring, that is, until your gaze shifts to the world beyond the glass next to you. He couldn’t help but to stare at how beautifully sculpted your face is. The Creator really made you look like the prettiest girl who had won his little contest of stealing his heart you didn’t know you had participated in. He looked away again when you turned back to look at him, never meeting his eyes and instead focusing on his chest. “Don’t stare at people. It’s rude and can spark lust, you know? And that is sinful.” She whispered to him quietly.

“I know.” Dan sighed, scratching the back of his neck to act sheepish after getting caught staring at her. “But, you look too beautiful, and I must admit that.” He told her.

When the atmosphere felt tensed, he rewinded time in his mind to see what had made her so quiet, and he widened his eyes when his mind registered what he said. “Gosh, I didn’t mean to say-!” He was cut off by her, whose eyes are teary and sad now for an unknown reason Dan has yet to figure out. “It’s okay.” He wanted to know why she’s upset, and so he made it as his goal to find out why and hopefully help her.

You could feel a weird thought coming from a deep part of your body, but you couldn’t register which part, and why you haven’t discovered it. When you finally registered what it is, you felt surprised by what it is. ‘I’ve seen the look on this man’s face, and I could tell how broken he is, how he’s fighting an invisible battle against something I have yet to figure out, and I know that I must help this man. I must fix him for him to function normally again, and maybe he can fix me back in return.’

Unbeknownst to you, your phone is sliding across the table, stopping in front of Dan’s drink. When you realised what happened, you widened your eyes in shock. “Put your number in my phone so that we can keep in contact, maybe become friends.”

You never fight alone.

Dan looked up at her in curiousity, his fingers quickly working on typing his number on the screen and giving her his own phone for her to do the same. When they took back their phones, Dan saw her smile genuinely at him. He could feel that she knows what he’s going through and what he’s battling against though they had never spoken of anything regarding that subject. She stood up, making him stand up too. “This is where I leave.” She gave him a small smile again before she took her first few steps out of the bubble they had formed, none of them realising that the bubble is pulling them closer to each other. He looked at his phone again, his own smile forming.

I’ll save you.
